import React from 'react'; const ProgramsSection = () => { return (

Our Programs

Menstrual Health Education

Workshops and awareness on hygiene and infections.

Reusable Pad Training

Empowering women with sewing and entrepreneurship skills.

Community Engagement

Mentorship and conversations to end menstrual stigma.

Sustainability Projects

Creating cooperatives for pad-making.

Projects Done or To Come

Completed: Maasai Community Workshop Series

2024

Conducted 15 workshops reaching 300+ Maasai girls and women, providing menstrual health education and reusable pad training.

Completed: Pad Distribution Program

2024

Distributed 2,000 reusable pads to Maasai communities in Kenya and Tanzania, with follow-up education sessions.

Ongoing: Entrepreneurship Training

2024-2025

Training 50 women in pad-making cooperatives, providing sewing skills and business development support.

Upcoming: School Partnership Program

2025

Partnering with 10 Maasai schools to integrate menstrual health education into curriculum and provide pad access.

Upcoming: Healthcare Provider Training

2025

Training local healthcare providers in menstrual health management and sustainable hygiene solutions.

Future: Regional Expansion

2025-2026

Expanding programs to additional Maasai communities across East Africa with scalable distribution models.

); }; export default ProgramsSection;
